'''Easter eggs''' were something found in a gigantic [[Ore/Legends|ore]] pipe on [[Mount Merakan]] when [[Nym/Legends|Nym]] flew inside it.

==Behind the scenes==
The name and titular objects are based on a practice done on Easter Sunday by Christians, which is creating colored eggs in celebration of the resurrection of Jesus Christ. Two types existed: One involved actual eggs that had their shells painted, and others were made of plastic and could be opened to find a treat inside, the latter also being the inspiration for [[Easter egg (virtual)|the video-game term]].

